{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "However, the citizen must have mechanisms to trust the drone's assertions that the data is sanitized.Pd-Ros is an exemplar framework aimed to provide such assurances on ROS2-based drones ( §4).",
    "ROS2-the Robot Operating System, version 2 [83]-is a popular middleware used in the software stacks of drones by numerous vendors.",
    "Pd-Ros enhances ROS2 to audit data flows between applications within the drone.",
    "Pd-Ros relies on trusted hardware on the delivery drone to provide the citizen with an audit trail of how their data is used within the drone.",
    "Many regulatory bodies do require delivery drones to be equipped with such trusted hardware (see §2 for references).Prior related methods in this area have been tailored toward ground-controlled drones [17,18,67,68]."
  ],
